## Phase 2: Context Summary Presentation (AI Presents, Human Reviews)

After gathering, AI **MUST** present a summary to the user in this structured format:

```markdown
## Task Context Summary

### Task Understanding
> [One paragraph summarizing the understanding of the task]

### Background Info
- [Key background extracted from docs/conversations, with links]

### Existing Design Decisions
| Document | Core Conclusion | Status |
|----------|-----------------|--------|
| [Path]   | [One sentence]  | [Done/WIP/TBD] |

### Code Dependencies
| Module | Path | Relationship |
|--------|------|--------------|
| [Name] | [Path]| [Depends on/Depended by/To modify] |

### Existing Rules
- [Any .mdc rules?] → [If yes, explain content]

### Past Conversations
- [Title](UUID) - [Core summary]

### Pending Confirmations
1. [Questions or assumptions for the user to confirm]
```

---

## Phase 3: Requirements Confirmation (Human Decision)

After presenting the summary, **wait for user confirmation**:

1. Is the task understanding accurate?
2. Clarify pending items one by one.
3. User decides the next direction.

**AI only answers questions and provides info here. Do NOT push forward proactively.**

