## Model Allocation Strategy (Cost Optimization)

### Core Principles

```text
Divide labor by cognitive type, not just price tiers:
  T1 Reasoning Models = "Thinking" tasks: design, planning, review, judging verification
  T2 Coding Models    = "Writing" tasks: programming, test implementation
  T3 Understanding    = "Reading" tasks: document comprehension, multimodal analysis
  T4 Fast Models      = "Running" tasks: search, git, file ops
```

### Auto-Downgrade (AI Executed)

In subagent tasks, **MUST** use `model="fast"` for:
- Phase 1 all context searches (grep, glob, git commands)
- Phase 4c mechanical tasks (git ops, running test commands, copying files)

### Manual Switch Prompts (AI MUST Prompt User)

When entering these stages, AI **MUST** remind the user to consider switching models:

```text
Entering dense coding/testing:
  "Next is dense coding. Consider switching to a faster coding model to save costs.
   We will return to the strongest reasoning model for code review afterward. Switch now?"

Coding finished, entering review:
  "Coding is done. Moving to code review and verification.
   Consider switching back to the strongest reasoning model for deep judgment. Switch now?"
```

### Model-Task Mapping Cheat Sheet

| Task Phase | Recommended Tier | Switch Method | Reason |
|------------|------------------|---------------|--------|
| Phase 1 Context Gathering | Fast | Auto (Subagent) | Search & match, no reasoning |
| Phase 2 Summary Gen | Reasoning | Keep Main | Synthesis & judgment |
| Phase 3 Confirmation | Reasoning | Keep Main | Understanding ambiguous intent |
| Phase 4a Path Selection| Reasoning | Keep Main | Architectural decision |
| Phase 4c Plan Breakdown| Reasoning | Keep Main | Requires architectural thinking|
| Phase 4c Dense Coding | Coding | **Prompt Manual Switch** | High code generation efficiency|
| Phase 4c Code Review | Reasoning | **Prompt Switch Back** | Deep judgment |
| Phase 4c Verification | Reasoning | **Prompt Switch Back** | Result analysis |
| Phase 4c Commands/Git | Fast | Auto (Subagent) | Mechanical execution |

